## The Cost of Paraphrasing

For developers, "it doesn't work" is not a statement but the start of a debugging marathon lasting several hours. One missing detail can mean the difference between 10 minutes and 10 hours of work.

When you paraphrase:

- Claude has to guess at the error type
- You lose searchable error codes
- Stack trace context disappears
- Multiple back-and-forth exchanges waste tokens and time
- The fix may address a different error than the one you have

When you copy verbatim:

- Claude sees exactly what you see
- Line numbers point to specific code
- Error codes match documentation
- First-response accuracy increases dramatically

## The Bottom Line

Error messages are precise for a reason. They contain exactly the information needed to diagnose the problem.

When you encounter an error, select everything from the error type to the last line of the stack trace. Copy it. Paste it into Claude exactly as it appears.

Your paraphrase loses information. The verbatim error contains the solution.
